<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1688,2038]" lastBlockId="3.[151,1437,153,791]" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="254" pageId="2" pageNumber="253">
Slender, well sclerotized dark brown larva, with short legs, antennae and cerci. All membranes covered by small branched sensilla (
<figureCitation box="[363,433,1904,1930]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1968,1993]" captionTargetBox="[237,1349,166,1941]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[237,1349,166,1949]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. Andiperla morenensis n. sp., male. 4a–b, detail of branched sensilla (chloride cells) on abdomen membrane, scanning microscope image." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3385683/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="253">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
). Head. Dorsally dark brown, mostly bare; ventrally light brown and poorly sclerotized, with many branched sensilla. Eyes big, protruding laterally, no ocelli. Cephalic suture well developed. Antennifer membranous, covered by branched sensilla. Antennae with 35–45 annuli, about as long as 3.2 max. head width, scape much larger than pedicel, which is larger than first annuli; flagellum annuli progressively thinner and slightly longer, with an apical ring of sparse short thick setae. Labrum trapezoidal, anterior margin wider, covered with hairlike setae longer on its anterior third and denser on the sides of anterior margin; anterior margin concave, lateral margins slightly concave. Right mandible (
<figureCitation box="[644,753,225,251]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1897,1922]" captionTargetBox="[192,1396,185,1871]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[189,1398,181,1871]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 4. Andiperla morenensis n. sp., male. 4a, right mandible, ventral view. 4b, left mandible, ventral view. 4c, right mandible, ventral view and detail of mola, scanning microscope image. 4d, left mandible, ventral view and detail of mola, scanning microscope image. 4e, maxilla, ventral view. 4f, maxilla, detail of palpus, lascinia and galea, ventral view. 4g, labium, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3385685/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="254">Fig. 4a, c</figureCitation>
) flat, with four teeth, three apical ones united at their base, the two apical ones the sharpest and largest, third one shorter and rounded; the fourth small; mola (
<figureCitation box="[1259,1340,261,287]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1897,1922]" captionTargetBox="[192,1396,185,1871]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[189,1398,181,1871]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 4. Andiperla morenensis n. sp., male. 4a, right mandible, ventral view. 4b, left mandible, ventral view. 4c, right mandible, ventral view and detail of mola, scanning microscope image. 4d, left mandible, ventral view and detail of mola, scanning microscope image. 4e, maxilla, ventral view. 4f, maxilla, detail of palpus, lascinia and galea, ventral view. 4g, labium, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3385685/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="254">Fig. 4c</figureCitation>
) simple, oval, concave, with fine ornamentation, ventro-basal margin with small teeth; dorso-apical surface of mandible covered by hair-like setae, turning to scale-like projections with acute apex towards the base; inner-basal margin with several long setae. Left mandible (
<figureCitation box="[538,648,369,396]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1897,1922]" captionTargetBox="[192,1396,185,1871]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[189,1398,181,1871]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 4. Andiperla morenensis n. sp., male. 4a, right mandible, ventral view. 4b, left mandible, ventral view. 4c, right mandible, ventral view and detail of mola, scanning microscope image. 4d, left mandible, ventral view and detail of mola, scanning microscope image. 4e, maxilla, ventral view. 4f, maxilla, detail of palpus, lascinia and galea, ventral view. 4g, labium, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3385685/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="254">Fig. 4b, d</figureCitation>
) flat, with four sharp teeth, two apical larger ones united at their base, and two shorter basal ones; mola (
<figureCitation box="[540,623,405,432]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1897,1922]" captionTargetBox="[192,1396,185,1871]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[189,1398,181,1871]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 4. Andiperla morenensis n. sp., male. 4a, right mandible, ventral view. 4b, left mandible, ventral view. 4c, right mandible, ventral view and detail of mola, scanning microscope image. 4d, left mandible, ventral view and detail of mola, scanning microscope image. 4e, maxilla, ventral view. 4f, maxilla, detail of palpus, lascinia and galea, ventral view. 4g, labium, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3385685/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="254">Fig. 4d</figureCitation>
) simple, oval, concave, with one apical triangular tooth, with fine ornamentation, dorsal margin with long acute projections; dorso-apical surface of mandible covered by hair-like setae, turning to scale-like projections with acute apex towards the base (
<figureCitation box="[915,999,477,503]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1897,1922]" captionTargetBox="[192,1396,185,1871]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[189,1398,181,1871]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 4. Andiperla morenensis n. sp., male. 4a, right mandible, ventral view. 4b, left mandible, ventral view. 4c, right mandible, ventral view and detail of mola, scanning microscope image. 4d, left mandible, ventral view and detail of mola, scanning microscope image. 4e, maxilla, ventral view. 4f, maxilla, detail of palpus, lascinia and galea, ventral view. 4g, labium, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3385685/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="254">Fig. 4c</figureCitation>
); inner-basal margin of mandible with several long setae. Maxilla (
<figureCitation box="[469,546,513,540]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1897,1922]" captionTargetBox="[192,1396,185,1871]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[189,1398,181,1871]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 4. Andiperla morenensis n. sp., male. 4a, right mandible, ventral view. 4b, left mandible, ventral view. 4c, right mandible, ventral view and detail of mola, scanning microscope image. 4d, left mandible, ventral view and detail of mola, scanning microscope image. 4e, maxilla, ventral view. 4f, maxilla, detail of palpus, lascinia and galea, ventral view. 4g, labium, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3385685/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="254">Figs. 4</figureCitation>
e–f) with a five-segmented palp, fifth palpomere the longest, proportions about 0,8:1:1,5:1,2:2; first and second palpomeres with a few setae and small branched sensilla. Galea long and curved inwards, with a few thin hair-like setae, apex square and with many long hair-like setae; lacinia approximately triangular, apex rounded, with no teeth, thin, spoon shaped with dorsal surface concave, with many hair-like setae on its inner margin, longer towards the apex. Labium (
<figureCitation box="[732,814,657,683]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1897,1922]" captionTargetBox="[192,1396,185,1871]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[189,1398,181,1871]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 4. Andiperla morenensis n. sp., male. 4a, right mandible, ventral view. 4b, left mandible, ventral view. 4c, right mandible, ventral view and detail of mola, scanning microscope image. 4d, left mandible, ventral view and detail of mola, scanning microscope image. 4e, maxilla, ventral view. 4f, maxilla, detail of palpus, lascinia and galea, ventral view. 4g, labium, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3385685/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="254">
Fig. 
<quantity box="[785,814,657,683]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="kg" metricValue="4.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="254" unit="g" value="4.0">4g</quantity>
</figureCitation>
) wider than long, with a three-segmented palp covered with several short hair-like setae, denser on distal palpomere, which is the longest, proportions about 1:0,7:0,45; glossa short, apex rounded and with a dense tuft of long hair-like setae, paraglossa long, spreading outwards, apex triangular and with a dense tuft of long hair-like setae on its outer margin.
</paragraph>
<caption httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3385681/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="254" startId="3.[151,250,1410,1435]" targetBox="[151,1436,805,1391]" targetPageId="3">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,1410,1471]" pageId="3" pageNumber="254">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,277,1410,1435]" pageId="3" pageNumber="254">FIGURE 2.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Pessacq &amp; Rivera-Pomar, 2019" authorityName="Pessacq &amp; Rivera-Pomar" authorityYear="2019" box="[285,509,1411,1435]" class="Insecta" family="Gripopterygidae" genus="Andiperla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="254" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="morenensis" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[285,509,1411,1435]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="254">Andiperla morenensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[517,576,1411,1435]" pageId="3" pageNumber="254">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[517,576,1411,1435]" pageId="3" pageNumber="254" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, female. 2a, abdominal segment IX–X, dorsal view. 2b, abdominal segment IX–X, lateral view. 2a, abdominal segment IX–X, ventral view.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1517,1940]" pageId="3" pageNumber="254">Thorax. Dorsally dark brown, mostly bare, margins with a row of short sparse spine-like setae; ventrally light brown, mostly membranous, covered by branched sensilla. Pronotum about 1.5 X as wide as long, maximum width about 0.6 X maximum head width, margins convex, angles rounded. Mesonotum about 1.6 X as wide as long, maximum width about 0.7 X maximum head width, anterior margin straight, lateral margins convex, posterior margin concave with rounded lateral projections resembling small wide and shallow wing pads. Metanotum about 1.4 X as wide as long, maximum width about 0.9 X maximum head width, margins as described in mesonotum. Legs: dark brown, short. Femora covered with few short spine-like setae, apex margin with a row of short spine-like setae, apex of flexor margin not sclerotized, forming a membranous V shaped area with branched sensilla, ventro-distal angle rounded; tibiae covered with short spine-like setae, denser than in femora, apex with a row of short spine-like setae, two small tibial spurs; tarsi covered by small spine-like setae, tarsal proportions as follows: 1:1:4; apex of tarsi with a row of short spine-like setae, distal tarsi with a weak ventral row of hair-like setae, four longer spine-like setae on extensor margin apex and one long hair-like seta on middle of extensor margin, tarsal claws acute.</paragraph>
<caption httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3385683/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="255" startId="4.[151,250,1968,1993]" targetBox="[237,1349,166,1941]" targetPageId="4">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,1968,2029]" pageId="4" pageNumber="255">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,275,1968,1993]" pageId="4" pageNumber="255">FIGURE 3.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[281,494,1969,1993]" class="Insecta" family="Gripopterygidae" genus="Andiperla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="255" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="morenensi">
<emphasis box="[281,494,1969,1993]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="255">Andiperla morenensi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
s 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[509,567,1969,1993]" pageId="4" pageNumber="255">n. sp.</emphasis>
, male. 4a–b, detail of branched sensilla (chloride cells) on abdomen membrane, scanning microscope image.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<caption httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3385685/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="256" startId="5.[151,250,1897,1922]" targetBox="[192,1396,185,1871]" targetPageId="5">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,1897,2030]" pageId="5" pageNumber="256">
